@NODE USAGE "Using PathPrefs"

   @{FG HIGHLIGHT}Using PathPrefs@{FG TEXT}

   Using PathPrefs is really simple. On starting the program (either from
   Workbench, CLI, or from within NetDock itself) a window will open
   containing 8 buttons, exactly the same as those within the main NetDock
   window. 

   Alongside each button will be a text field containing a program path.
   For example, in the default paths, the first location is 'Miami:Miami'.

   To change a location, just click on the appropriate image button.
   PathPrefs checks to see if the file exists, so don't worry about
   getting duff path files.

   To save your changes, just goto the menus (RMB!) and select Save Paths
   from the menu.


   THAT'S ALL THERE IS TO KNOW!
@ENDNODE
